  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "roIjJC0MAn27no2nJFoJiDrYfis=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:44.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# Skip Field and Deterministic Conflict Resolution\n\nWhen Alice and Bob edit the same cell concurrently, both ops get written to their respective op feeds with `skip: 0`. When each reactor receives the other's op, the SyncManager runs deterministic conflict resolution.\n\n## Algorithm\n\n1. Detect conflict: same document, overlapping timestamps\n2. Reshuffle operations by sorting on `(timestamp, operationId)` for total order\n3. Assign new global indices and update `skip` values\n4. Replay through the document model reducer\n\n## Example outcome\n\n```\nIndex  Skip  Action             Origin\n  6     0    SET_CELL(A1,100)   Alice\n  7     1    SET_CELL(A1,200)   Bob\n```\n\n`skip=1` on Bob's op means: \"this op was reshuffled past 1 other op.\"\n\n## Convergence guarantee\n\nSame ops + same ordering rule = same final state on every device. No CRDTs required \u2014 the document model reducer plus deterministic replay is sufficient.\n",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:44.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:44.000Z"
    }
  },
